id: pm-qt5d
title: Project package install with --pm-path can write extensions into the caller workspace
description: "Manual temp-workspace dogfood on 2026-07-04 found that running node dist/cli.js --pm-path <temp>/.agents/pm install '*' --project from the repository cwd installed bundled extensions into the caller repository tracker .agents/pm/extensions before cleanup, even though the requested tracker path was the temp tracker. This is a path-scoping UX/safety bug for agents testing package installs from a repo checkout. Expected: explicit --pm-path project-scope package installs write only under that pm root or fail with a clear workspace-root guard. Actual: the temp tracker received installed packages, but the caller workspace tracker also got extension files/managed-extension churn."
type: Issue
status: open
priority: 2
tags[4]: agent-ux,dogfood,extensions,path-safety
created_at: "2026-07-04T11:25:59.083Z"
updated_at: "2026-07-04T19:17:26.665Z"
author: claude-code-agent
estimated_minutes: 90
acceptance_criteria: A regression test covers pm install '*' --project with --pm-path pointing at a temp tracker while cwd is another initialized repo; no files are written under the caller repo .agents/pm/extensions and the command output makes the target pm root unambiguous.
parent: pm-mpbb
risk: medium
confidence: high
comments[2]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-04T11:25:59.083Z",claude-code-agent,"Duplicate check before creation: searched all statuses for 'install pm-path project scope writes cwd tracker', 'package install --pm-path --project', and 'with-packages bundled package install tracker path'. Closest hits were closed pm-r0m4 (CJS type:module activation), closed pm-hosd (init --with-packages), and open pm-b3e9 (pre-install command hints); none track explicit --pm-path project install writing into the caller workspace tracker."
  "2026-07-04T11:42:53.708Z",claude-code-agent,"Evidence: created as follow-up only after explicit all-status duplicate checks. The current branch cleaned accidental local .agents/pm/extensions output from manual dogfood and does not implement this path-safety fix; acceptance remains open for a targeted regression."
body: "## Context\n2026-07-04 temp-workspace dogfood: `node dist/cli.js --pm-path <temp>/.agents/pm install '*' --project` run from the repo checkout wrote bundled extensions into the CALLER repo's .agents/pm/extensions (managed-extensions churn) as well as the temp tracker. Path-scoping safety bug: an explicit --pm-path must confine ALL writes to that pm root.\n\n## Suspected cause\nPackage install resolves the project extension target from cwd/workspace discovery instead of the effective pm root passed via --pm-path (install pipeline and extension-manager paths diverge).\n\n## Approach\nThread the resolved pm root through the install/extension-write path; add a guard that refuses (or warns loudly) when an install would write outside the requested root. Regression spec: run install with --pm-path pointing at a temp tracker from a cwd that has its own tracker; assert the caller tracker is byte-identical before/after.\n\n## Definition of done\nThe exact dogfood repro leaves the caller workspace untouched; guard covered by spec; note in EXTENSIONS.md that --pm-path scopes package installs."
